INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(146, 2, '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '<h1>Paraplegia Injury</h1>\nIf you are a victim of an accident that results in paraplegia, an experienced personal injury attorney can represent you in court and help you receive appropriate compensation for your damages. Paraplegia can be a devastating outcome of a spinal cord injury and many people never fully recover. The Law Office of David Azizi specializes in paraplegia injury and spinal injury cases. We have helped many clients receive the support and compensation they deserve so that they can lead a comfortable and healthy lifestyle after their traumatic experience.\n\n<h3>Common Causes of Paraplegia </h3>\n\nParaplegia is a lower injury that affects the legs and lower parts of the body. The injury can result in complete loss of sensation in the lower body, and the inability to move certain limbs and muscles. More serious cases result in loss of bladder control and improper bowel functioning, and these serious conditions rarely improve over the course of the victim’s life. Any excessive damage to the spinal cord can lead to paraplegia. The common accidents that cause paraplegia are:\nAuto accidents\nMotorcycle or bike accidents\nDiving injuries\nSporting accidents\nPedestrian accidents\nConstruction accidents\n\nThe medical expenses that result from paraplegia can be a financial burden for most individuals and their families.\n\n<h3>Working with a Paraplegia Attorney </h3>\n\nThe professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com have extensive experience in paraplegia injuries and accidents that result in spinal cord injuries. We will do everything legally possible to aggressively pursue your case to obtain the maximum recovery you deserve. We understand how difficult it can be to work with insurance companies who will only agree to pay a very small portion of your medical expenses. Most people simply cannot afford to manage these exorbitant costs on their own, and must resort to personal loans, credit cards and other financial resources just to pay their medical bills.\n\nOur experienced legal professionals will take the time to investigate your case, contact witnesses from the accident, work with medical professionals to assess your condition, and build a solid case for a claim or lawsuit.\n\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can provide you with immediate assistance. We will not charge you any fees until your case is resolved.', 'Paraplegia Injuries', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'paraplegia-injuries', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '2013-04-30 06:55:35', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=146', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(148, 2, '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '<h1>Pedestrian Accidents</h1>\nPedestrian accidents are some of the most common cases involved in our cities, and most are the result of driver negligence and failure to observe the pedestrian right-of-way. If you are involved in a pedestrian accident that results in hospitalization or severe injuries, you will need the assistance of a personal injury lawyer to represent your case. The Law Office of David Azizi has extensive experience in handling pedestrian accident cases and will take the time to evaluate the damages, gather testimonies from witnesses and even reconstruct the scene of the accident in order to pursue your case vigorously.\n\n<h3>Understanding Pedestrian Accidents </h3>\n\nSituations that may be defined as a pedestrian accident include:\nBeing struck by a car\nBeing hit by a bus\nBeing struck by a truck or motorcycle\nPoor property maintenance that results in a fall\nTending to a crash on the interstate, highway or road\n\n<h3>What to Do When You are Involved in a Pedestrian Accident </h3>\n\nIn some cases, it can be difficult to assess whether the pedestrian accident was the result of somebody else’s negligence or the pedestrian’s own fault. No matter what the circumstance may be, it is important that you:\nContact the police department to report the accident\nStay at the scene of the accident until help arrives\nObtain any names and phone numbers of witnesses at the scene\nCall an experienced personal injury attorney from AziziPersonalInjury.com as soon as possible to report the event\n\nBeing involved in a pedestrian accident can be a very distressing experience, and you may not have the resources or energy to return to work and pay your medical bills.\n\n<h3>Work with an Experienced Pedestrian Accident Attorney </h3>\n\nAziziPersonalInjury.com has the experience and knowledge to litigate pedestrian accident cases. We understand how challenging it can be to work with insurance companies that want a quick settlement and do not take your short-term and long-term interests into account. We make sure we do everything possible to cover all of the details of the case and help you receive full compensation for all expenses related to the incident.\n\nContact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can discuss your case. AziziPersonalInjury.com is determined to aggressively pursue your case, and we will not charge you a single dollar until the matter is fully resolved.', 'Pedestrian Accidents', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pedestrian-accidents', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '2013-04-30 06:56:45', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=148', 0, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES(150, 2, '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '<h1>Quadriplegia Injury</h1>\nOne of the most tragic and physically devastating injuries someone can endure is a quadriplegia injury. Quadriplegia injuries can result in a lifetime of pain and discomfort as the victim loses all sensation and the ability to move their four limbs. If you or a loved one have become quadriplegic as a result of an accident or negligence, you will need the assistance of an experienced quadriplegia attorney to handle your case. The professionals at AziziPersonalInjury.com have extensive experience in representing quadriplegia cases, and can provide guidance and support when you need to file a claim or lawsuit.\n\n<h3>Common Causes of Quadriplegia </h3>\n\nQuadriplegia is also known as ‘tetraplegia’, and is the complete paralysis of all four limbs as a result of severe spinal damage. Serious cases rarely improve over time, and the victim typically needs extensive medical care and attention throughout the course of his or her life. Excessive damage to the spinal cord can be a result of several types of accidents and injuries such as:\nAutomobile accidents\nConstruction or on-the-job incidents\nMotorcycle or biking accidents\nSporting accidents\nDefective products\n\nThe medical expenses and rehabilitative care involved with taking care of a quadriplegic can put a financial strain on any family or victim. Working with an experienced quadriplegia lawyer from the Law Office of David Azizi means you can count on professional legal representation to recover compensation for your damages which you deserve.\n\n<h3>Working with a Quadriplegia Attorney </h3>\n\nWe have extensive experience in representing clients involved in personal injury cases and specialize in injuries related to spinal cord damage. We will do everything legally possible to aggressively pursue your case and to ensure that you and your family are not taken advantage of by insurance companies and medical providers.\n\nYou don’t have to resort to personal loans, credit cards or other financial resources just to cover the cost of medical bills; allow our quadriplegia attorneys to assess your case and assist you with receiving adequate and fair compensation for your damages.\n\nAt AziziPersonalInjury.com, we take the time to investigate your case and aggressively litigate your claim order to build a solid case against the offending party. Contact us today for a free, no obligation consultation so that we can determine the best course of action for your quadriplegia case. We will not charge you a single dollar until your case is resolved.', 'Quadriplegia Injuries', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'quadriplegia-injuries', '', '', '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '2013-04-30 06:57:43', '', 0, 'http://azizipersonalinjury.com/main/main/?page_id=150', 0, 'page', '', 0);
